	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Boston</placeName>&#44; <date>Mai 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1848</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">An illness prevented me to write to you<lb/> any sooner.  Nothing very important happened here.<lb/>  The following officers were elected at the general meeting on <date>April 23rd</date>.</p>
				<list type="simple">
				<head></head>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. M. Ehrlich</persName>&#44;   Pres.</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>H. P. Spitz</persName>&#44;   <sic>Vize</sic> Pres. &#38; Treas.</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>C. W. Rosenfeld</persName>  <add>Trustee</add></item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>S. M. Peyser </persName>  <add>Trustee</add></item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>M. Baiersdorfer</persName>  Trustees</item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>M. Disbecker</persName>   <add>Trustee</add></item>
					<item rend="indent(1)"><persName>H. Selling</persName>   <add>Trustee</add></item>
				<item>and <persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName>   Secretary</item>
				</list>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Several members of our congre&#45;<lb/>gation suggested the introduction of a 3 year c<del>i</del>ycle&#44;<lb/> which of course means the abolition of the record<lb/> holiday and other reforms.  This of course caused<lb/> hot debates&#44; as could be expected particularly from the<lb/> Non German group.  I believe&#44; however&#44; that this<lb/> plan will be adopted at the next G. M. on<lb/> <date>July 2nd</date>&#41; my religion school impresses widely.<lb/>  Owing to the kind <del>support</del> collaboration of a lady&#44; <persName>Mrs<lb/> Lazarus</persName>&#44; we have now nice<add>&#63;</add> &#38; weeks a</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p rend="align(center)">2</p>
				<p>Sunday school and all of us tie by &#40;story&#41;<lb/> expectations to it for this lady really justifies my<add>&#63;</add><lb/> expectations&#44; for she has a wide knowledge&#44; a<lb/> wonderful Jewish heart and a distinct preference<lb/> to teach.  May the Lord bless her undertaking<lb/> and may her seeds open<add>&#63;</add> in the heart of our children.<lb/> <add>Hevvah Ahavath Ahoth &#40;the last word is wrong&#41;</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Our Ladies Hebrew Benevolent <del>An</del><lb/> Society had its G. M. yesterday &#40;this society exist<lb/> now exactly one year and <del>has been</del> I was the one<lb/> who brought it to life&#41;.  <persName>Mr. B. Fox</persName> became Pres.<lb/> and <persName>Mr. L. Lervingood</persName> became Vice Pres. And<lb/> Treas. And <persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName> was the Secretary.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">How is your &#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;<add>Tefiloth</add><lb/> according the&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;<add>Minhag &#40;ritual&#41;</add> of the German Jews<lb/> getting along&#63;  I am anxiously waiting.<lb/>  Please forward 10 copies and of course<lb/> one free copy as soon as you get through<lb/> with it.  You forgot <del>to Attach your</del> bill in your<lb/> parcel containing <sic>chatechisms</sic> for young children.<lb/>  Please forward by return mail 3 more copies together<lb/> with your bill for all six.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you have <add>alphabet <add>Hebrew</add> </add><lb/> books&#44; please send 6 copies along with them.<lb/>  If you don&#39;t have them let me know where I can</p>
			<pb n="3R"/>
				<p>get them.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">No more for today.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">B. Wurmser</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>No. 8 Pleasant Street<lb/></placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Court</placeName></p>	
				<p>PS. I expect the books by<lb/> <persName>Harnden&#39;s &#38; Co.</persName> Express<lb/> in a short time</p>
		</body>
